  "doc_id": "30623",
  "text": "Recently, acetaminophen and aspirin were confined on the nanoscopic level to influence their nucleation. By variation in the pore size of the polymeric template gels, the nucleation rates of these drugs were optimized. The pore size of the template gels was easy to manipulate to modify pore size, thus, control the nucleation step. Nanoconfinement could make a significant contribution to rational crystallization process design in the future as the nucleation step can now be controlled [CITATION_1] .",
